The paper discusses the use of multidimensional databases in On-line Analytical Processing (OLAP), which is a common application in the field of database management (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of caching and compression methods to improve performance, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper proposes models for evaluating the performance of different physical representations, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or software engineering (cs.SE).
